      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BLACKPOOL FINN (5) flew the lids with a strong early split and led throughout to score an impressive win by 2.5 lengths over 400m at this track (22.62). Ran the fastest time on the program in his latest win. Makes plenty of appeal on the back of that last-start win. MISS JO (2) returned a better run last time, finishing in the money (25.39) at Ballarat behind Elite Intention in a Grade 4/5. Has the early speed to give a sight. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings three times from six attempts. Hard to beat again. STILL BELIEVE (4) got the job done again after leading to make it back to back wins at this track over 460m (26.12). Winner at her latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. Has definite claims. MAC AND CHEESE (1) is in the mix despite finishing out of the placings here last start.",
